cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.DS

This paper deals with machine learning algorithms for anti-money laundering, which involves classification and risk scoring. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses data collection and labeling, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
